HOW TO START
- npm i -g --save-dev jest
- change package.json
    "scripts": {
        "test": "jest"
    }
- always create test script with postfix .test.js
    ex. functions.test.js
    NOTE: running npm test will automatically locate functions.test.js and run

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

jest/functions.js
    - this file contains functions need to be test
jest/functions.test.js
    - this file contains script for testing the functions
    - notice the filename has postfix .test.js in order or jest to read that this file is for testing.

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

TO RUN JEST
type "npm test" in the terminal

- take note the all jest command/scripts can be seen in the internet, just search the google
